ng their achievements, and dismantling harmful stereotypes in a way that resonates with her generation. Her moderate openness to new experiences suggests that targeted outreach programs, utilizing digital channels, could effectively engage young girls in STEM, offering them role models and inspiring them to dream big.  Ultimately, bridging the gender gap in science isn't just about numbers; it's about unlocking the full potential of humanity. It's about recognizing that every voice matters, every perspective is valuable, and every individual has the capacity to contribute to a brighter, more inclusive scientific future.",
